This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically focusing on neural language models such as Word2Vec. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses modifications to the standard architecture of Word2Vec, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses background knowledge from a previously learned semantic space, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses a nonce task involving context, which could potentially fall under computer vision (cs.CV).
